	"metadata": {
		"title": "unbound: unrestricted reconfiguration enabled to anyone that may lead to local privilege escalation (important)",
		"reference": [
			{
				"ref_id": "CVE-2024-1488",
				"ref_url": "https://access.redhat.com/security/cve/CVE-2024-1488",
				"source": "CVE"
			}
		],
		"description": "DOCUMENTATION: A vulnerability was found in Unbound due to incorrect default permissions, allowing any process outside the unbound group to modify the unbound runtime configuration. If a process can connect over localhost to port 8953, it can alter the configuration of unbound.service. This flaw allows an unprivileged attacker to manipulate a running instance, potentially altering forwarders, allowing them to track all queries forwarded by the local resolver, and, in some cases, disrupting resolving altogether.",
